{% call components.section("Responsive design") -%}

  <h4>Ordering</h4>

  <p>When call to action links are grouped together, they are ordered by hierarchy from left to right. On small screens, the order changes to <strong>left to right and top to bottom</strong> if there are call to action links that fall into a second row.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-responsive-design-ordering.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component responsive design, ordering" style="--inline-img-max-width: 750px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Long text labels</h4>

  <p>Long text labels will wrap to two lines on small screens or when translated to certain languages. This can be avoided by writing less text or revising existing text to be shorter.</p>

  <!-- Temporary Warning alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #fdf7e7; border-top: 2px solid #f0ab00; padding: 16px 16px 16px 24px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;"><span style="color:#795600"><strong>Warning</strong></span><br />The Default call to action link arrow should not appear by itself, it should always be connected to at least one word on the same line.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-responsive-design-long-text-labels.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component responsive design, long text labels" style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Brick</h4>

  <p>The Brick variants will move around the grid to accommodate different container sizes.</p>

  <!-- Temporary Warning alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #fdf7e7; border-top: 2px solid #f0ab00; padding: 16px 16px 16px 24px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;"><span style="color:#795600"><strong>Warning</strong></span><br />Long text labels might break to two lines which adds height and disrupts the grid, therefore write <strong>no more than two or three words</strong> per link.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--0">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-responsive-design-brick.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component responsive design, ordering" style="--inline-img-max-width: 1000px;">
  </div>

{%- endcall %}

{% call components.section("Best practices") -%}

  <h4>Changing styles</h4>

  <p>Do not modify the styles of any variant for any reason.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-bestpractice-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component, best practice 1" style="--example-img-max-width: 598px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Too many links</h4>

  <p>Do not group more than three variants together otherwise a user might have trouble making a selection if there are too many link choices.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-bestpractice-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component, best practice 2" style="--example-img-max-width: 635px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Using multiple Primary variants</h4>

  <p>Do not use multiple Primary variants in the same group, use of that variant is reserved to represent the most important link.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-bestpractice-3.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component, best practice 3" style="--example-img-max-width: 305px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Mixing variant groups</h4>

  <p>Do not group more than two variants together anywhere.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-bestpractice-4.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component, best practice 4" style="--example-img-max-width: 405px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Mixing Bricks</h4>

  <p>Do not group different Brick variants together anywhere, use one only.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-bestpractice-5.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component, best practice 5" style="--example-img-max-width: 552px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Changing hierarchy</h4>

  <p>Do not change the hierarchy when grouping, variants that are higher in hierarchy should go first.</p>

  <!-- Temporary Warning alert until web component release -->
  <p style="background-color: #fdf7e7; border-top: 2px solid #f0ab00; padding: 16px 16px 16px 24px; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;"><span style="color:#795600"><strong>Warning</strong></span><br />Do not change the hierarchy when grouping unless the change is to accommodate right-to-left languages.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-bestpractice-6.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component, best practice 6" style="--example-img-max-width: 690px;">
  {%- endcall %}

  <h4>Stretching</h4>

  <p>Do not stretch any other variants to fit a container or grid, only the Brick variants can stretch.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <img src="{{ '/assets/cta/cta-bestpractice-7.svg' | url }}" alt="Call to action component, best practice 7" style="--example-img-max-width: 664px;">
